HEADWORD: Long-sufferance
<hw>Long"-suf`fer*ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Forbearance to punish or resent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>patient endurance of pain or unhappiness.</def>⟦br⟧
